# Phase 1: Database Schema

## Context

- [plan.md](./plan.md)
- [Prisma schema](../../backend/prisma/schema.prisma)
- [Code standards - DB](../../docs/code-standards.md)

## Overview

Add a `Theme` model to Prisma with all color/style fields. Seed a default theme marked as `active`.

## Key Insights

- Existing models use UUID PKs, snake_case columns, `@@map` for table names, `@@schema("public")`
- No enum needed for status -- use a `Boolean isActive` field (simpler than string enum for single-active)
- A `slug` field enables URL-friendly identification and prevents duplicate names
- Color fields stored as individual String columns (not JSON) for type safety and direct query

## Requirements

- Theme model with all visual customization fields
- Default theme seeded with values matching current `globals.css`
- Only one theme can have `isActive = true` at a time (enforced at application level)

## Architecture

```
Theme (themes)
  id           UUID PK
  name         String
  slug         String @unique
  description  String?
  isActive     Boolean @default(false)

  -- Colors --
  primaryColor       String? @default("#205")       -> maps to --primary
  secondaryColor     String? @default("#970")
  accentColor        String? @default("#970")
  backgroundColor    String? @default("#ffffff")
  textColor          String? @default("#1f2937")
  primaryForeground  String?
  borderColor        String?

  -- Assets --
  logoUrl      String?
  faviconUrl   String?

  -- Advanced --
  customCss    String? @db.Text
  fontFamily   String?

  -- Timestamps --
  createdAt    DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt    DateTime @updatedAt
```

## Related Code Files

- `/home/trung/workspace/project/private/tiny-lms/backend/prisma/schema.prisma`

## Implementation Steps

- [ ] Add `Theme` model to `schema.prisma` following existing conventions
- [ ] Create migration: `npx prisma migrate dev --name add_themes`
- [ ] Create seed script or SQL to insert default theme with `isActive = true`
- [ ] Run `npx prisma generate`

### Prisma Model

```prisma
model Theme {
  id                  String    @id @default(uuid()) @db.Uuid
  name                String
  slug                String    @unique
  description         String?
  isActive            Boolean   @default(false) @map("is_active")

  // Colors
  primaryColor        String?   @map("primary_color")
  secondaryColor      String?   @map("secondary_color")
  accentColor         String?   @map("accent_color")
  backgroundColor     String?   @map("background_color")
  textColor           String?   @map("text_color")
  primaryForeground   String?   @map("primary_foreground")
  borderColor         String?   @map("border_color")

  // Assets
  logoUrl             String?   @map("logo_url")
  faviconUrl          String?   @map("favicon_url")

  // Advanced
  customCss           String?   @map("custom_css") @db.Text
  fontFamily          String?   @map("font_family")

  createdAt           DateTime  @default(now()) @map("created_at")
  updatedAt           DateTime  @updatedAt @map("updated_at")

  @@index([isActive])
  @@schema("public")
  @@map("themes")
}
```

### Seed SQL

```sql
INSERT INTO themes (id, name, slug, is_active, primary_color, secondary_color, accent_color, background_color, text_color, created_at, updated_at)
VALUES (
  gen_random_uuid(), 'Default', 'default', true,
  '#3b82f6', '#8b5cf6', '#10b981', '#ffffff', '#1f2937',
  now(), now()
)
ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
```

